Name: curiosity IOU
Comment:
PLEASE READ AND SPREAD THIS INFORMATION.
They are making it look like these laws were going to destroy their lives. When people ask about the concerns of farmers all they give is speculation. "Ye HOGA wo HOGA aisa HOGA ye Modi ye karna CHATA HAI REAL ME etc."

govt during negotiations offered them a
- promise to not destroy MSP mechanism,
- they offered them civil court like grievance redress mechanisms.
- They offered free legal representation to farmers in event of corporate disputes,
- they offered to withdraw the bill for a year and a half and talk about modification in the bill with farmers unions during that time.

Even SC stayed the laws until itтАЩs panel decides on constitutionality of the laws. There were 9 round of talks held between the farmers and officials and ministers. But farmers have just chose to stuck with 2 demands ..
1 withdraw the bill.
And 2 guarantee MSP.

GUARANTEEING MSP will cost the government an additional 10lakh crore or more .The country just does not have that kind of money. That would be 50% of IndiaтАЩs annual expenditure used to procure food.
The MSP declared are always above than the world market prices so guaranteeing them essentially will kill agricultural exports of India. Also govt provides support to farmers via electricity subsidy, fertilizer subsidy and farm loan waivers. ItтАЩs a no brainier for any person with understanding of economics that farm loan waivers are one of the worst economic moves this country has been taking for years and why? Because votes. So essentially politicians buy votes in the garb of farm loan waivers.

So much favor is already given by the government that more than 30% of what is investing in agriculture by farmers to grow crops is payed by government. Then they pay the farmers to procure 7% of India total agricultural produce via MSP mechanism. The number might look less but That costs the government around 1 lakh crore rupees a year. Then they sell these procured food at ration shops via PDS mechanism at throw away prices like Rs.3 a kilo for wheat when market price is 23 rupees To ensure that poor sections of the country are fed. IN WTO countries sue INDIA because world thinks that India subsidizes farmer produce too much. Unfair trade practice they say .49% of the population is involved in farming in India and not .1% farmers are protesting the bill. Out of 28 states only farmers of Haryana and Punjab has problems. You know why? Because 87% of govt procurement via MSP mechanism is done through Punjab and Haryana.

And in rest all other states APMC is basically suffocating marginal and small farmers. Marginal and small farmers by the way are 86% of farming population in India. So sis you tell me now why do you think govt is not backing out? And forget farmers knowing all I mentioned above even educated people taking stands on the issue are barely half aware of how bad Indian agriculture sector of India is. In the whole globe there is no other prominent country that spends 15% of its GDP. granted There are countries that spend more percentage of GDP. Some go as high as 40%. But they donтАЩt have 2 hostile nuclear nations that forces country to have one of the largest standing army world has ever seen. They have about 200mil old people whom they give pension. 350mil poor whom we give shelter and food. They pay for the massive administrative machinery that keeps the country of 1.3bil people intact and running. There is health, education, and other 60+ welfare schemes running for the betterment of people. The math just donтАЩt add up. It is easy for people to think govt is this and that. But how many in that crowd is really aware of the things I wrote above? Truth is the only wrong government did was the arbitrary nature of the introduction of these farm bills. The arrogance with which they introduced it. However even there if we investigate we can see the oppositions contributed to this direction of government by always creating ruckus in parliamentary sessions instead of having debate and discussions. It is just sad that since independence agriculture is growing at a rate of 2.6%a year. During British raj it grew at 1.7%. This stat alone should raise eye brows.

Knowing all this I just donтАЩt know with whom I should side with because honestly, majority of people in the protest believe that they are right but in reality they are pawn in the hands of people with vested agendas. They are pawns because they lack awareness. Every event boils down to this one factor only. And still people donтАЩt hesitate forming opinions and taking stands and fighting other believing they are right which just complicated things.
